Question 
create 2D numpy  based array with given conditions:

i)   take input from user in terms of dimension like (3x2 or 6x7)
ii)   fill this numpy array with random number
iii)  store this array in a file
Solution 
#!/usr/bin/python3
import numpy as np
a=int(input("enter the no of rows"))                #To take integer input from user
b=int(input("enter the no of column"))
e = np.random.random((a,b)) 
print ("\nA random array:\n", e) 
np.save(outfile, e)
np.load(outfile)


